episodes.plot: Leslie competes with a tech company for land, which she wants to turn into a national park.

episodes.title: Ron & Jammy
episodes.plot: Leslie and Ron help councilman Jamm escape Tammy's evil clutches, April decides to pursue a new career, and Tom and Andy go to Chicago after Tom receives a message from one of his exes.

episodes.title: William Henry Harrison
episodes.plot: Leslie tries to find a historical connection to enhance the National Parks Service's bid, while Ron's group counters with a celebrity investor.

episodes.title: Leslie and Ron
episodes.plot: The gang locks Leslie and Ron in the old Parks Department office overnight and force them to settle their differences and end their feud.

episodes.title: Gryzzlbox
episodes.plot: Leslie and Ben think Gryzzl is illegally data-mining Pawnee residents, Tom helps Andy try to get the rights to his "Johnny Karate" TV character, and April encourages an intern to quit the Parks Department.

episodes.title: Save JJ's
episodes.plot: In hope of keeping JJ's diner open, Leslie organizes a rally; Tom has a surprise gift for Donna.

episodes.title: Donna and Joe
episodes.plot: On the night before Donna and Joe's wedding, Ben receives an offer to run for Congress and Ron causes a problem for Tom's new relationship.

episodes.title: Ms. Ludgate-Dwyer Goes to Washington
episodes.plot: During a business trip to Washington, April tells Leslie that she wants to quit her job. Back in Pawnee, Andy, Ben and Ron may have found her the perfect new job.

episodes.title: Pie-Mary
episodes.plot: A traditional pie-baking competition causes problems for Ben's campaign, Ron goes on a scavenger hunt to find one of his house keys that April lost, and Gary loses his wedding ring in a drain outside the building.

episodes.title: The Johnny Karate Super Awesome Musical Explosion Show
episodes.plot: The last episode of Andy's TV show brings his friends together.

episodes.title: Two Funerals
episodes.plot: Ben has to appoint a new mayor after mayor Gunderson dies, Ron grieves over the death of his barber, and Leslie helps Tom set up a predictably over-the-top marriage proposal.

episodes.title: One Last Ride
episodes.plot: As the team gathers one final time before they go their separate ways, we look 10 years into the future for each team member.
